    <field id="homePageContent" text-type="text/html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-250"></h1><p id="polarion_new_0">
  Test Specification collects test cases that are intended to be used to test a software feature or combination of software features and specifies the details of the test approach.
</p><div id="polarion_wiki macro name=toc"></div><h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-251"></h2><h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-252"></h3><p id="polarion_merged_1">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">Identify the purpose of this Test Specification document and its intended audience.</span>
</p><h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-253"></h3><p id="polarion_merged_2">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">Provide a short description of the test.</span>
</p><h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-254"></h3><p id="polarion_merged_3">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">List any other documents or Web addresses to which this test specification document refers. Provide enough information so that the reader could access a copy of each reference, including title, author, version number, date, and source or location.Example: reference the <span id="WIKI_LINK:Test Plan|Test Plan"></span>, if it exists.</span>
</p><h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-255"></h2><p id="polarion_merged_4">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">Identify the test items and describe the features and combinations of features that are the object of this specification. Other features may be exercised, but need not be identified.For each feature or feature combination, a reference to its associated requirements in the item requirement specification or design description should be included.</span>
</p><h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-256"></h2><p id="polarion_merged_5">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">Specify refinements to the approach described in the test plan. Include specific test techniques to be used. The method of analyzing test results should be identified (e.g., comparator programs or visual inspection).</span>
</p><h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-257"></h2><div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-333"></div><h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=WI-334"></h2><p id="polarion_merged_0">
  <span style="font-style: italic;">Define all the terms necessary to properly interpret this document, including acronyms and abbreviations. You may wish to build a separate glossary that spans multiple projects or the entire organization, and just include terms specific to a single project in each document.</span>
</p>]]></field>
